OL,3,C'A system in crisis': Inside NI's
OL,4,Csocial care system
OL,6,F"While significant and necessary work
OL,7,Fhas been undertaken by many committed
OL,8,Findividuals involved in the Programme,
OL,9,Fthe number of children who are looked
OL,10,Fafter continues to grow, and families
OL,11,Fcontinue to be referred to children's
OL,12,Fsocial care services broadly in
OL,13,Fsimilar numbers as before.
OL,15,F"We need to be able to slow, and in
OL,16,Ftime, reverse that trend. That will
OL,17,Frequire us to provide greater and
OL,18,Fearlier help to families who are
OL,19,Fstruggling.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G14/21
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
